												<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/hannahzeavin/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Zeavin_2022-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Zeavin_2022-300x300.jpeg 2x" alt="Hannah Zeavin" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
												<div class="description author withsidebar">
													<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/hannahzeavin/">Hannah Zeavin</a></h6>
													Hannah Zeavin is Assistant Professor of the History of Science in the Department of History and the Berkeley Center for New Media at UC Berkeley. She is the author of <em>The Distance Cure</em> (MIT Press) and Founding Editor of <em>Parapraxis</em>. In 2021, she cofounded The Psychosocial Foundation.																									</div>
											</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
										</div>

